      "component": "Maladaptive Strategies",
      "item": "Other-Blame Rumination: I dwell on what other people have done to me",
      "explanation": "This item contradicts the trauma type of bereavement. Bereavement typically involves loss rather than interpersonal harm where others are to blame. The presence of this item alongside 'Hypervigilance towards people' suggests a trauma involving intentional harm by others, which is inconsistent with bereavement as the primary trauma type."
    },
    {
      "component": "Maladaptive Strategies",
      "item": "Hypervigilance towards people: vigilant for dangerous people",
      "explanation": "This item is inconsistent with bereavement trauma. Hypervigilance for dangerous people implies a threat of interpersonal violence or harm, which doesn't align with the nature of bereavement. This would be more appropriate for assault, combat, or other interpersonal trauma types."
    }
